  2. What plots does the following code make? What does . do? > The period makes it not facet in a row/column dimension

  3. What are the advantages to using faceting instead of the colour aesthetic? What are the disadvantages? How might the balance change if you had a larger dataset? >The advantage of faceting data could makes it easier to see values within categories, but too many categories may make the graph difficult to read.

  4. Read ?facet_wrap. What does nrow do? What does ncol do? What other options control the layout of the individual panels? Why doesn’t facet_grid() have nrow and ncol arguments? >nrow/ncolumn displays the number of rows or columns. as.table default will lay out facets as a table with the highest values in the bottom right. facet_grid() doesn’t have rows or columns because it is not a table.

  5. When using facet_grid() you should usually put the variable with more unique levels in the columns. Why? >To differentiate between values
